CODE STYLE
==========


This file describe a code style ....


1. Header on each file

/*
 * @author: Name of original author
 * @description: a short description of the file
 * @date: creation date
 *
 * More detailed description (optional)
 *
 * CHANGES
 * - dd/mm/yy - short description
 * - dd/mm/yy - short description
 * - dd/mm/yy - short description
 *
 */



2. Identifiers

- Functions and variables name in lower case
- more_than_one_word identifiers separeted by underline
- CONSTANTE upper case


3. Identation

- Use just ONE tab per identation (not spaces)
- Use spaces just do alignment


4. Braces

- Braces after functions MUST be placed at a new line:

function foo()
{
	
}

- All others open braces (if, for, switch, while so on) are at the end of line:

if (true) {
	/* foo */
}

for (i = 0; i < sz; i++) {
	/* bar */
}


5. Comments

- Function in a header file (.h) MUST be prepended by the follow header:

/**
 * Short description of function
 *
 * @param   first   meaning of parameter 'fist'
 * @param   second  meaning of parameter 'second'
 * @param   third   meaning of parameter 'third'
 *
 * @return          meaning of return value
 *           0      meaning of return value 0
 *           1      meaning of return value 1
 *           CONST  meaning of return value CONST
 *
 * More detailed description (optional)
 */